translate:
Fine brocade and silk, the Tartar boy's skin is black as lacquer;
Riding on ice, he shoots like an arrow, riding the sheep with ease.
Honey wine and white birds, grape wine and red wax;
Sweet alfalfa roots, sand mice come out to play.
The Odorless Arm of the Khan, why should it be severed?
The bright sun shines upon the Emperor, just as it does upon the heavens.
A grip of black beard, a grip of silk threads;
You must know that all this is for the art of peace.
